    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
      "name": "Drink Blood",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Requirement </strong>A @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Grabbed]{Grabbed}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Paralyzed]{Paralyzed}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Restrained]{Restrained}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Unconscious]{Unconscious}, or willing creature is within the manananggal's reach.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The manananggal sinks its fangs into that creature to drink its blood. This requires an Athletics check against the victim's Fortitude DC if the victim is grabbed and is automatic for any of the other conditions. The victim is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Drained]{Drained 1} and the manananggal regains 5 HP, gaining any excess HP as temporary Hit Points. Drinking Blood from a creature that's already drained doesn't restore any HP to the manananggal but increases the victim's drain value by 1.</p>\n<p>A victim's drained condition decreases by 1 per week. A blood transfusion, which requires a @Check[type:medicine|dc:20] check and sufficient blood or a blood donor, reduces the drain by 1 after 10 minutes.</p>"
        },
